subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: On the accompanying map of North and South America: Indicate by arrows the main coastal currents and drifts north of the Equator, and name them. Delimit carefully two areas of tropical grasslands and two of temperate grasslands, marking each “tropical” or “temperate” as the case may be. Name each of the grasslands shown.
